caption:
//Adaptability// • Circumstances have pushed many suppliers to turn to B2C e-commerce to keep in the green. It's entertaining to see the amount of premium ingredients we now have at the tip of our fingers. Take @yakiniku_plaza for example, purveyor of Japanese Wagyu and Kobe beef who were responsible for bringing A4 Japanese Wagyu Karubi straight to my kitchen!

Without deliberating, I decided to prepare a simple Wagyu Karubi ($24/100g) don to showcase its marbled beauty. Quick pickled carrots, onsen tamago, ginger roasted broccoli and onions braised in soy and mirin to accompany the seared slices.

Visit https://yakinikuplaza.com.sg/ to shop for your wagyu needs to fit any shabu shabu, sukiyaki or yakiniku occasion. They are currently doling out $12 off your total bill for a min. spend of $80. Promo code: [NICE2MEATU]. #sskitchendisasters #fundamentallyflawedkitchen #food52 #StayHomeWithAscott

